{{unreferenced|date=November 2015}} [[File:Shock gum.jpg|thumb|A packet of shock chewing gum]] '''Shocking gum''' is a [[practical joke device]] that delivers a mild [[electric shock]]. The victim is offered a stick of gum from a box, and touching this triggers the shock. A few novelty companies in the 1950s produced these 'Shocking gum' packages. The most popular brands of Shocking Gum are ''Fruit Juicy'' and ''JB''.
In 2005, the US Military reported that insurgents in Iraq were using shock chewing gum as a form of torture, forcing prisoners to bite down on the sticks.<ref>{{cite web |title=Shock Gum photo |url=https://www.2ndmardiv.marines.mil/Photos/igphoto/144211/ |website=www.2ndmardiv.marines.mil}}</ref>
